                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">White</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-07-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1368.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose copies of two dispatches from the
                    consul-general at Frankfort-on-the-Main, relative to the defilement of the coat
                    of arms of the United States at the United States consulate at Bamberg.</p>
                <p>A new coat of arms will be sent for the use of the consulate at Bamberg, and you
                    will ask for its admission free of duty.</p>
            </div>
